{:metadata {:description [{"text" "<p>This entry represents a family of proteins mainly found in actinomycetes, including thioredoxin-like reductase Rv2466c from Mycobacterium tuberculosis. Rv2466c is a key oxidoreductase that mediates the reductive activation of TP053, a thienopyrimidine derivative that kills replicating and non-replicating M.tuberculosis. This enzyme transforms nitro-containing compounds to their corresponding amine and uses as a cofactor, a low molecular weight sugar thiol, mycothiol. This protein adopts a thioredoxin-like fold and forms a unique homodimer in which the C-terminal Î²-strand is swapped between the thioredoxin domains of each subunit [[cite:PUB00154218], [cite:PUB00154217], [cite:PUB00154219]]. Rv2466c undergoes significant conformational changes upon formation of its oxidised state [[cite:PUB00154217]].</p>", "llm" false, "checked" false, "updated" false}], :is-reviewed-llm false, :representative-structure {"accession" "4nxi", "name" "Rv2466c Mediates the Activation of TP053 To Kill Replicating and Non-replicating Mycobacterium tuberculosis"}, :overlaps-with [{"accession" "IPR036249", "name" "Thioredoxin-like superfamily", "type" "homologous_superfamily"}], :member-databases {"pfam" {"PF22234" "Mycothiol-dependent nitroreductase Rv2466c"}}, :is-updated-llm false, :name {"name" "Thioredoxin-like reductase Rv2466c-like", "short" "Rv2466c-like"}, :wikipedia nil, :source-database "interpro", :type "family", :counters {"structures" 4, "domain_architectures" 9, "proteomes" 1679, "taxa" 4838, "subfamilies" 0, "interactions" 0, "matches" 7085, "sets" 0, "proteins" 7082, "structural_models" {"alphafold" 5466}, "pathways" 0}, :integrated nil, :cross-references {}, :set-info nil, :accession "IPR053977", :literature {"PUB00154217" {"URL" nil, "issue" "52", "authors" ["Albesa-Jove D" "Comino N" "Tersa M" "Mohorko E" "Urresti S" "Dainese E" "Chiarelli LR" "Pasca MR" "Manganelli R" "Makarov V" "Riccardi G" "Svergun DI" "Glockshuber R" "Guerin ME.